This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama commemorating the 150th anniversary of the Civil War. The proclamation highlights the significance of the Civil War in shaping the United States and emphasizes the sacrifices made by millions of Americans during the conflict. It also acknowledges the progress made in extending equal rights to all citizens through constitutional amendments. The proclamation calls on Americans to observe the Sesquicentennial with appropriate programs and activities that honor the legacy of freedom and unity.